<!--             displacement, -->
velocity, 
<!--             speed,  -->
            and acceleration at <m>2</m>
seconds. Use appropriate units for each.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
A widget is sold for <m>\$96</m> per item. Suppose that the number of items produced is equal to the number of items sold and that
the cost (in dollars) of producing <m>x</m> widgets is given by the
following function:
<me>C(x)=5 \, x^{3} + 9 \, x^{2} + x + 4.</me>
                </p>
                <p>
 
Explain and demonstrate how to find the marginal revenue, the marginal cost, and the marginal profit
in this situation.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
The equation of the tangent line is <m>y = 3 \, x + 30</m>.
                </p>
            </li>
                    
            <li>
        <ul>
